The purpose of this study is to examine whether exergame use can improve user health, in terms of physical fitness, self-rated mental health and physical health, and favorable attitude, strong intention, and actual behavior of future exercise.

 Moreover, this study also examines whether past exercise moderates the impact of exergame use on user health.

